mscX25DteRowStatusTable.name: mscX25DteRowStatusTable
mscX25DteRowStatusTable.description: This entry controls the addition and deletion of mscX25Dte components.

mscX25DteRowStatusEntry.name: mscX25DteRowStatusEntry
mscX25DteRowStatusEntry.description: A single entry in the table represents a single mscX25Dte component.

mscX25DteRowStatus.name: mscX25DteRowStatus
mscX25DteRowStatus.description: This variable is used as the basis for SNMP naming of mscX25Dte components. These components can be added and deleted.

mscX25DteComponentName.name: mscX25DteComponentName
mscX25DteComponentName.description: This variable provides the component's string name for use with the ASCII Console Interface

mscX25DteStorageType.name: mscX25DteStorageType
mscX25DteStorageType.description: This variable represents the storage type value for the mscX25Dte tables.

mscX25DteIndex.name: mscX25DteIndex
mscX25DteIndex.description: This variable represents the index for the mscX25Dte tables.

mscX25DteCidDataTable.name: mscX25DteCidDataTable
mscX25DteCidDataTable.description: This group contains the attribute for a component's Customer Identifier (CID). Refer to the attribute description for a detailed explanation of CIDs.

mscX25DteCustomerIdentifier.name: mscX25DteCustomerIdentifier
mscX25DteCustomerIdentifier.description: This attribute holds the Customer Identifier (CID). Every component has a CID. If a component has a cid attribute, the component's CID is the provisioned value of that attribute; otherwise the component inherits the CID of its parent. The top- level component has a CID of 0. Every operator session also has a CID, which is the CID provisioned for the operator's user ID. An operator will see only the stream data for components having a matching CID. Also, the operator will be allowed to issue commands for only those components which have a matching CID. An operator CID of 0 is used to identify the Network Manager (referred to as 'NetMan' in DPN). This CID matches the CID of any component. Values 1 to 8191 inclusive (equivalent to 'basic CIDs' in DPN) may be assigned to specific customers.

mscX25DteIfTable.name: mscX25DteIfTable
mscX25DteIfTable.description: This group provides the administrative set of parameters for the X.25 interface.

mscX25DteInterfaceMode.name: mscX25DteInterfaceMode
mscX25DteInterfaceMode.description: This attribute specifies the packet mode in which the X.25 interface operates. When this attribute is set to dte, interface on the other side of the physical link must be configured as a dce.

mscX25DteMaxActiveChannels.name: mscX25DteMaxActiveChannels
mscX25DteMaxActiveChannels.description: This attribute specifies the maximum number of channels that can be active on this interface including the Permanent Lcns and the Switched Lcns. In total maxActiveChannel will determine the maximum number of Lcn components which may exist at a given time. This should be set to a value greater or equal to the numberOfPLcn provisioned.

mscX25DteNumberOfPLcn.name: mscX25DteNumberOfPLcn
mscX25DteNumberOfPLcn.description: This attribute specifies the number of Permanent Logical Channels that are supported on this X.25 interface (that is, the number of PermLcn components that may be provisioned at this interface). The PermLcn components use channel numbers starting from 1 and up to lowestILChannelNumber. A value of 0 for this attribute indicates that no Permanent Logical channels are supported on this X.25 interface.

mscX25DtePacketSequencing.name: mscX25DtePacketSequencing
mscX25DtePacketSequencing.description: This attribute specifies the sequence numbering of packets for the X.25 interface. The value of this attribute must be the same as the packet sequencing configured at the X.25 interface on the other side of the physical link.

mscX25DteT20RestartTimer.name: mscX25DteT20RestartTimer
mscX25DteT20RestartTimer.description: This attribute provides the period in milliseconds within which a restart request packet should be confirmed.

mscX25DteT21CallTimer.name: mscX25DteT21CallTimer
mscX25DteT21CallTimer.description: This attribute provides the period in milliseconds within which a call request packet should be confirmed.

mscX25DteT22ResetTimer.name: mscX25DteT22ResetTimer
mscX25DteT22ResetTimer.description: This attribute provides the period in milliseconds within which a reset request packet should be confirmed.

mscX25DteT23ClearTimer.name: mscX25DteT23ClearTimer
mscX25DteT23ClearTimer.description: This attribute provides the period in milliseconds within which a clear request packet should be confirmed.

mscX25DteLcnCTable.name: mscX25DteLcnCTable
mscX25DteLcnCTable.description: This group contains the provisionable attributes for the Logical Channel configuration of the X.25 Interface. The logical channel range table is ordered as follows: Permanent Logical Channels(PLC), One-way Incoming Channels (IC), Two-way Channels(TC) and One-way Outgoing Channels (OC), in a consecutive manner.

mscX25DteLowestILChannelNumber.name: mscX25DteLowestILChannelNumber
mscX25DteLowestILChannelNumber.description: This attribute specifies the lowest Lcn number of the One-way Incoming Channel range for this X.25 interface. The value for this attribute must be greater than the numberOfPLcn attribute.

mscX25DteHighestILChannelNumber.name: mscX25DteHighestILChannelNumber
mscX25DteHighestILChannelNumber.description: This attribute specifies the highest Lcn number of the One-way Incoming Channel range for this X.25 interface. A value of 0 indicates that there are no channels in this range.

mscX25DteLowestTLChannelNumber.name: mscX25DteLowestTLChannelNumber
mscX25DteLowestTLChannelNumber.description: This attribute specifies the lowest Lcn number of the Two-way Channel range for this X.25 interface. The value for this attribute must be greater than the highestILChannelNumber attribute.

mscX25DteHighestTLChannelNumber.name: mscX25DteHighestTLChannelNumber
mscX25DteHighestTLChannelNumber.description: This attribute specifies the highest Lcn number of the Two-way Channel range for this X.25 interface. A value of 0 indicates that there are no channels in this range.

mscX25DteLowestOLChannelNumber.name: mscX25DteLowestOLChannelNumber
mscX25DteLowestOLChannelNumber.description: This attribute specifies the lowest Lcn number of the One-way Outgoing Channel range for this X.25 interface. The value for this attribute must be greater than the highestTLChannelNumber attribute.

mscX25DteHighestOLChannelNumber.name: mscX25DteHighestOLChannelNumber
mscX25DteHighestOLChannelNumber.description: This attribute specifies the highest Lcn number of the One-way Outgoing Channel range for this X.25 interface. A value of 0 indicates that there are no channels in this range.

mscX25DteDcpTable.name: mscX25DteDcpTable
mscX25DteDcpTable.description: This group contains the provisionable attributes giving the default call parameters used by all the logical channels during call setup. It is possible that different default call parameters will be used for a particular call, based on the Peer component for the given call. The actual call parameters operational for a given call are found in the Lcn component.

mscX25DteInPacketSize.name: mscX25DteInPacketSize
mscX25DteInPacketSize.description: This attribute specifies the maximum receive packet size in octets for the X.25 interface.

mscX25DteOutPacketSize.name: mscX25DteOutPacketSize
mscX25DteOutPacketSize.description: This attribute specifies the maximum transmit packet size in octets for the X.25 interface.

mscX25DteInWindowSize.name: mscX25DteInWindowSize
mscX25DteInWindowSize.description: This attribute specifies the maximum receive window size for the X.25 interface. A window size greater than 7 is only valid when the packetSequencing attribute is set to modulo128.

mscX25DteOutWindowSize.name: mscX25DteOutWindowSize
mscX25DteOutWindowSize.description: This attribute specifies the maximum transmit window size for the X.25 interface. A window size greater than 7 is only valid when the packetSequencing is set to modulo128.

mscX25DteAcceptReverseCharging.name: mscX25DteAcceptReverseCharging
mscX25DteAcceptReverseCharging.description: This attribute specifies whether local end will accept or refuse charges for a call. A value of neverAccept is only used at the X.25 interface level and indicates that this interface will never accept reverse charging (that is no Peer component can override this parameter, allowing reverse charged calls to be accepted).

mscX25DteProposeReverseCharging.name: mscX25DteProposeReverseCharging
mscX25DteProposeReverseCharging.description: This attribute specifies whether local/reverse charging is signalled in the call request packet.

mscX25DteOutThroughputClassSize.name: mscX25DteOutThroughputClassSize
mscX25DteOutThroughputClassSize.description: This attribute specifies the value of the transmit throughput class to be negotiated. A value of notSpecified means the facility is not signalled.

mscX25DteInThroughputClassSize.name: mscX25DteInThroughputClassSize
mscX25DteInThroughputClassSize.description: This attribute specifies the value of the receive throughput class to be negotiated. A value of notSpecified means the facility is not signalled.

mscX25DteCugIndex.name: mscX25DteCugIndex
mscX25DteCugIndex.description: This attribute specifies the index of the Closed User Group facility to signal. The index consists of two or four octets each representing a digit in the range of 0 to 9. A value of null (empty string) at the X.25 interface means no CUG facility is signalled. If a cugIndex is provisioned to be signalled, the cugoaIndex attribute must be null.

mscX25DteCugoaIndex.name: mscX25DteCugoaIndex
mscX25DteCugoaIndex.description: This attribute specifies the index of the Close User Group with Outgoing Access facility to signal. The index consists of two or four octets each representing a digit in the range of 0 to 9. A value of null (empty string) at the X.25 interface means no CUGOA facility is signalled. If a cugoaIndex is provisioned to be signalled, the cugIndex attribute must be null.

mscX25DteChargingInformation.name: mscX25DteChargingInformation
mscX25DteChargingInformation.description: This attribute specifies whether the charging information facility is to be signalled in a call request packet. A value of notSpecified means the facility is not signalled. A value of notRequested means the facility is signalled but charging information is not requested (that is, the charging info field of the facility is set Off). A value of requested means the facility is signalled to explicitly request charging information.

mscX25DteRpoa.name: mscX25DteRpoa
mscX25DteRpoa.description: This attribute specifies the value of the RPOA facility to signal in a call request packet. The value of null (empty string) at the X.25 interface means no RPOA facility is signalled.

mscX25DteTrnstDlySlctnAInd.name: mscX25DteTrnstDlySlctnAInd
mscX25DteTrnstDlySlctnAInd.description: This attribute specifies the value of the Transit Delay Selection and Indication facility to signal in a call request packet. A value of 65536 at the X.25 interface level means no TDSAI facility is signalled.

mscX25DteCallingNetworkFax.name: mscX25DteCallingNetworkFax
mscX25DteCallingNetworkFax.description: This attribute specifies the Calling Network facilities to be signalled in a call request packet. A value of null (empty string) at the X.25 interface means no facilities are signalled.

mscX25DteCalledNetworkFax.name: mscX25DteCalledNetworkFax
mscX25DteCalledNetworkFax.description: This attribute specifies the called network facilities to be signalled in a call request packet. A value of null (empty string) at the X.25 interface means no facilities are signalled.

mscX25DteCallUserData.name: mscX25DteCallUserData
mscX25DteCallUserData.description: This attribute specifies the user data to be signalled in the call request packet. A value of null (empty string) means no user data is signalled.

mscX25DteIfEntryTable.name: mscX25DteIfEntryTable
mscX25DteIfEntryTable.description: This group contains the provisionable attributes for the ifEntry.

mscX25DteIfAdminStatus.name: mscX25DteIfAdminStatus
mscX25DteIfAdminStatus.description: The desired state of the interface. The up state indicates the interface is operational. The down state indicates the interface is not operational. The testing state indicates that no operational packets can be passed.

mscX25DteIfIndex.name: mscX25DteIfIndex
mscX25DteIfIndex.description: This is the index for the IfEntry. Its value is automatically initialized during the provisioning process.

mscX25DteStateTable.name: mscX25DteStateTable
mscX25DteStateTable.description: This group contains the three OSI State attributes. The descriptions generically indicate what each state attribute implies about the component. Note that not all the values and state combinations described here are supported by every component which uses this group. For component-specific information and the valid state combinations, refer to NTP 241-7001-150, Passport Operations and Maintenance Guide.

mscX25DteAdminState.name: mscX25DteAdminState
mscX25DteAdminState.description: This attribute indicates the OSI Administrative State of the component. The value locked indicates that the component is administratively prohibited from providing services for its users. A Lock or Lock - force command has been previously issued for this component. When the value is locked, the value of usageState must be idle. The value shuttingDown indicates that the component is administratively permitted to provide service to its existing users only. A Lock command was issued against the component and it is in the process of shutting down. The value unlocked indicates that the component is administratively permitted to provide services for its users. To enter this state, issue an Unlock command to this component.

mscX25DteOperationalState.name: mscX25DteOperationalState
mscX25DteOperationalState.description: This attribute indicates the OSI Operational State of the component. The value enabled indicates that the component is available for operation. Note that if adminState is locked, it would still not be providing service. The value disabled indicates that the component is not available for operation. For example, something is wrong with the component itself, or with another component on which this one depends. If the value is disabled, the usageState must be idle.

mscX25DteUsageState.name: mscX25DteUsageState
mscX25DteUsageState.description: This attribute indicates the OSI Usage State of the component. The value idle indicates that the component is not currently in use. The value active indicates that the component is in use and has spare capacity to provide for additional users. The value busy indicates that the component is in use and has no spare operating capacity for additional users at this time.

mscX25DteOperStatusTable.name: mscX25DteOperStatusTable
mscX25DteOperStatusTable.description: This group includes the Operational Status attribute. This attribute defines the current operational state of this component.

mscX25DteSnmpOperStatus.name: mscX25DteSnmpOperStatus
mscX25DteSnmpOperStatus.description: The current state of the interface. The up state indicates the interface is operational and capable of forwarding packets. The down state indicates the interface is not operational, thus unable to forward packets. testing state indicates that no operational packets can be passed.

mscX25DteOpTable.name: mscX25DteOpTable
mscX25DteOpTable.description: This group contains the operational status of the X.25 interface.

mscX25DteInterfaceState.name: mscX25DteInterfaceState
mscX25DteInterfaceState.description: This attribute specifies the state of the interface. The notReady state, is the initial state of the service, when it is being initialized. The localRestarting state is entered when a Restart packet is sent to the link and the interface is waiting for a response. The remoteRestarting state is entered when a Restart packet is received from the link, and is being processed. In ready state, the service is operational and ready to provide service.

mscX25DteStatsTable.name: mscX25DteStatsTable
mscX25DteStatsTable.description: This component contains the statistics for the X.25 interface.

mscX25DteInCalls.name: mscX25DteInCalls
mscX25DteInCalls.description: This attribute counts the number of call packets received from link.

mscX25DteInCallRefusals.name: mscX25DteInCallRefusals
mscX25DteInCallRefusals.description: This attribute counts the number of calls received from the link which have been cleared. This includes calls cleared by the X.25 interface and calls cleared by the higher level.

mscX25DteInPrvdrInitiatedClrs.name: mscX25DteInPrvdrInitiatedClrs
mscX25DteInPrvdrInitiatedClrs.description: This attribute counts the number of clear packets received from the link with a cause code other than DTE initiated.

mscX25DteInRmtInitiatedRsts.name: mscX25DteInRmtInitiatedRsts
mscX25DteInRmtInitiatedRsts.description: This attribute counts the number of reset packets received from the link with the cause code DTE initiated.

mscX25DteInPrvdrInitiatedRsts.name: mscX25DteInPrvdrInitiatedRsts
mscX25DteInPrvdrInitiatedRsts.description: This attribute counts the number of reset packets received from the link with the cause code other than DTE initiated.

mscX25DteInRestarts.name: mscX25DteInRestarts
mscX25DteInRestarts.description: This attribute counts the number of restart packets received from the link while the service is in ready state.

mscX25DteInDataPackets.name: mscX25DteInDataPackets
mscX25DteInDataPackets.description: This attribute counts the number of data packets received from link.

mscX25DteInPktsAcusdOfPrtclErr.name: mscX25DteInPktsAcusdOfPrtclErr
mscX25DteInPktsAcusdOfPrtclErr.description: This attribute counts the number of clear, reset, restart and diagnostic packets received from link containing a procedure error cause code.

mscX25DteInInterruptPackets.name: mscX25DteInInterruptPackets
mscX25DteInInterruptPackets.description: This attributes counts the number of interrupt packets received from link.

mscX25DteOutCallAttempts.name: mscX25DteOutCallAttempts
mscX25DteOutCallAttempts.description: This attribute counts the number of call packets sent from this interface.

mscX25DteOutCallFailures.name: mscX25DteOutCallFailures
mscX25DteOutCallFailures.description: This attribute counts the number of call attempts from this interface that failed. This includes calls that were cleared because of restrictive fast select.

mscX25DteOutInterruptPackets.name: mscX25DteOutInterruptPackets
mscX25DteOutInterruptPackets.description: This attribute counts the number of interrupt packets sent to the link.

mscX25DteOutDataPackets.name: mscX25DteOutDataPackets
mscX25DteOutDataPackets.description: This attribute counts the number of data packets sent to the link.

mscX25DteOutActiveChannels.name: mscX25DteOutActiveChannels
mscX25DteOutActiveChannels.description: This attribute indicates the number of One-way Outgoing Channels that are currently in use. This counter includes the call requests that have not been accepted.

mscX25DteInActiveChannels.name: mscX25DteInActiveChannels
mscX25DteInActiveChannels.description: This attribute indicates number of One-way Incoming Channels that are currently active.

mscX25DteTwowayActiveChannels.name: mscX25DteTwowayActiveChannels
mscX25DteTwowayActiveChannels.description: This attribute indicates the number of Two-way Channels that are in use. This includes call requests sent but not yet accepted.

mscX25DteT20RestartTimeouts.name: mscX25DteT20RestartTimeouts
mscX25DteT20RestartTimeouts.description: This attribute counts the number of times the T20 restart timer has expired.

mscX25DteT21CallTimeouts.name: mscX25DteT21CallTimeouts
mscX25DteT21CallTimeouts.description: This attribute counts the number of times the T21 call timer has expired.

mscX25DteT22ResetTimeouts.name: mscX25DteT22ResetTimeouts
mscX25DteT22ResetTimeouts.description: This attribute counts the number of times the T22 reset timer has expired.

mscX25DteT23ClearTimeouts.name: mscX25DteT23ClearTimeouts
mscX25DteT23ClearTimeouts.description: This attribute counts the number of times the T23 clear timer has expired.

mscX25DtePeerRowStatusTable.name: mscX25DtePeerRowStatusTable
mscX25DtePeerRowStatusTable.description: This entry controls the addition and deletion of mscX25DtePeer components.

mscX25DtePeerRowStatusEntry.name: mscX25DtePeerRowStatusEntry
mscX25DtePeerRowStatusEntry.description: A single entry in the table represents a single mscX25DtePeer component.

mscX25DtePeerRowStatus.name: mscX25DtePeerRowStatus
mscX25DtePeerRowStatus.description: This variable is used as the basis for SNMP naming of mscX25DtePeer components. These components can be added and deleted.

mscX25DtePeerComponentName.name: mscX25DtePeerComponentName
mscX25DtePeerComponentName.description: This variable provides the component's string name for use with the ASCII Console Interface

mscX25DtePeerStorageType.name: mscX25DtePeerStorageType
mscX25DtePeerStorageType.description: This variable represents the storage type value for the mscX25DtePeer tables.

mscX25DtePeerIndex.name: mscX25DtePeerIndex
mscX25DtePeerIndex.description: This variable represents the index for the mscX25DtePeer tables.

mscX25DtePeerIfTable.name: mscX25DtePeerIfTable
mscX25DtePeerIfTable.description: This group provides the administrative set of parameters for the Peer interface.

mscX25DtePeerEncAddressType.name: mscX25DtePeerEncAddressType
mscX25DtePeerEncAddressType.description: This attribute specifies the encapsulation type for the address of the remote host with which this Peer component allows communication.

mscX25DtePeerEncAddress.name: mscX25DtePeerEncAddress
mscX25DtePeerEncAddress.description: This attribute specifies the encapsulation address of the remote host with which this Peer component allows communication. This address must correspond with the encapsulation address type. Thus in the case of IP, it will contain a IP address.

mscX25DtePeerX25Address.name: mscX25DtePeerX25Address
mscX25DtePeerX25Address.description: This attribute specifies the X.25 address that identifies the remote host with which this Peer component allows communication. The remote X.25 interface could be subdivided through the use of RemoteGroup components; in which case this x25Address is the X.25 address of the destination's RemoteGroup (not to be confused with the RemoteGroup indicated by the linkToRemoteGroup attribute of THIS Peer component).

mscX25DtePeerLinkToRemoteGroup.name: mscX25DtePeerLinkToRemoteGroup
mscX25DtePeerLinkToRemoteGroup.description: This is a link to a RemoteGroup component. The RemoteGroup components logically divide up the X.25 Interface such that a number of Protocol Ports (and consequently a number of Virtual Routers) may share the same X.25 Interface into a Wide Area Network. In particular, the remote host identified by this Peer component is designated as belonging to the RemoteGroup linked by this attribute. The set of all Peer components and PermLcn components which link to a given RemoteGroup determine the subset of remote hosts which are accessible to a particular Protocol Port (and ultimately a Virtual Router).

mscX25DtePeerCpTable.name: mscX25DtePeerCpTable
mscX25DtePeerCpTable.description: This group contains the call parameters used to establish a call to/ from the remote host identified by this Peer component

mscX25DtePeerInPacketSize.name: mscX25DtePeerInPacketSize
mscX25DtePeerInPacketSize.description: This attribute specifies the default maximum receive packet size in octets. A setting of 0 indicates the inPacketSize setting for the X.25 interface (in X25Dte component) is used during call setup to the remote host identified by this Peer component.

mscX25DtePeerOutPacketSize.name: mscX25DtePeerOutPacketSize
mscX25DtePeerOutPacketSize.description: This attribute specifies the default maximum transmit packet size in octets. A setting of 0 indicates the outPacketSize setting for the X.25 interface (in the X25Dte component) is used during call setup to the remote host identified by this Peer component.

mscX25DtePeerInWindowSize.name: mscX25DtePeerInWindowSize
mscX25DtePeerInWindowSize.description: This attribute specifies the default receive window size. A window size of 0 indicates the inWindowSize setting for the X.25 interface (in the X25Dte component) is used during call setup to the remote host identified by this Peer component. A window size greater than 7 is only valid when the packetSequencing attribute of the X25Dte component is set to modulo128.

mscX25DtePeerOutWindowSize.name: mscX25DtePeerOutWindowSize
mscX25DtePeerOutWindowSize.description: This attribute specifies the default transmit window size. A window size of 0 indicates the outWindowSize setting for the X.25 interface is used during call setup to the Peer identified by this component. A window size greater than 7 is only valid when the packetSequencing attribute of the X25Dte component is set to modulo128.

mscX25DtePeerAcceptReverseCharging.name: mscX25DtePeerAcceptReverseCharging
mscX25DtePeerAcceptReverseCharging.description: This attribute specifies whether the local end will accept or refuse charges for a call from the remote host identified by this Peer component. A value of default indicates the use of the acceptReverseCharging value from the X25Dte component. If the value at the X25Dte level is neverAccept, a value of accept in this Peer component will be ignored because no reverse charge calls are to be accepted by this X.25 Dte.

mscX25DtePeerProposeReverseCharging.name: mscX25DtePeerProposeReverseCharging
mscX25DtePeerProposeReverseCharging.description: This attribute specifies whether local/reverse charging is signalled in a call request packet. A value of default indicates the use of the value from the proposeReverseCharging attribute of the X25Dte component.

mscX25DtePeerOutThroughputClassSize.name: mscX25DtePeerOutThroughputClassSize
mscX25DtePeerOutThroughputClassSize.description: This attribute specifies the value of the transmit throughput class to be negotiated. A value of default indicates the use of the value from the outThroughputClassSize attribute of the X25Dte component. A value of notSpecified means the facility is not signalled.

mscX25DtePeerInThroughputClassSize.name: mscX25DtePeerInThroughputClassSize
mscX25DtePeerInThroughputClassSize.description: This attribute specifies the value of the receive throughput class to be negotiated. A value of default indicates the use of the value from the inThroughputClassSize attribute of the X25Dte component. A value of notSpecified means the facility is not signalled.

mscX25DtePeerCugIndex.name: mscX25DtePeerCugIndex
mscX25DtePeerCugIndex.description: This attribute specifies the index of the Closed User Group facility to signal. A value of 'DEF' indicates the use of the value from the cugIndex attribute of the X25Dte component. A value of null (empty string) indicates no CUG facility is to be signalled. If a cugIndex is provisioned to be signalled, the cugoaIndex attribute must be null.

mscX25DtePeerCugoaIndex.name: mscX25DtePeerCugoaIndex
mscX25DtePeerCugoaIndex.description: This attribute specifies the index of the Closed User Group with Outgoing Access facility to signal. A value of 'DEF' indicates the use of the value from the cugoaIndex attribute of the X25Dte component. A value of null (empty string) indicates no CUGOA facility is to be signalled. If a cugoaIndex is provisioned to be signalled, the cugIndex attribute must be null.

mscX25DtePeerNetworkUserIdentifier.name: mscX25DtePeerNetworkUserIdentifier
mscX25DtePeerNetworkUserIdentifier.description: This attribute specifies the Network User Identifier facility to signal. A value of null (empty string) indicates no NUI facility is to be signalled.

mscX25DtePeerChargingInformation.name: mscX25DtePeerChargingInformation
mscX25DtePeerChargingInformation.description: This attribute specifies whether the charging information facility is signalled in the call request packet. A value of default indicates the use of the value from the chargingInformation attribute of the X25Dte component. A value of notSpecified means the facility is not signalled. A value of notRequested means the facility is signalled but charging information is not requested (that is, the charging info field of the facility is set Off). A value of requested means the facility is signalled to explicitly request charging information.

mscX25DtePeerRpoa.name: mscX25DtePeerRpoa
mscX25DtePeerRpoa.description: This attribute specifies the RPOA facility to signal in a call request packet. A value of 'DEF' indicates the use of the value from the rpoa attribute of the X25Dte component. A value of null (empty string) indicates no RPOA facility is to be signalled.

mscX25DtePeerTrnstDlySlctnAInd.name: mscX25DtePeerTrnstDlySlctnAInd
mscX25DtePeerTrnstDlySlctnAInd.description: This attribute specifies the value of the Transit Delay Selection and Indication facility to signal in a call request packet. A value of 65536 indicates no facility is signalled. A value of 65537 indicates the use of the value from the trnstDlySlctnAInd attribute of the X25Dte component.

mscX25DtePeerCallingNetworkFax.name: mscX25DtePeerCallingNetworkFax
mscX25DtePeerCallingNetworkFax.description: This attribute specifies the Calling Network facilities to signal in a call request packet. The facilities are encoded here exactly as they are encoded in the call packet. These facilities do not include the marker facility code. A value of null (empty string) indicates the callingNetworkFax from the X25Dte are to be signalled. If that value is also null, no Calling Network Facilities are signalled.

mscX25DtePeerCalledNetworkFax.name: mscX25DtePeerCalledNetworkFax
mscX25DtePeerCalledNetworkFax.description: This attribute specifies the Called Network facilities to signal in a call request packet. The facilities are encoded here exactly as they are encoded in the call packet. These facilities do not include the marker facility code. A value of null (empty string) indicates the calledNetworkFax from the X25Dte are to be signalled. If that value is also null, no Called Network Facilities are signalled.

mscX25DtePeerCallUserData.name: mscX25DtePeerCallUserData
mscX25DtePeerCallUserData.description: This attribute specifies the user data to signal in a call request packet. A value of null (empty string) indicates that the callUserData from the X25Dte is to be signalled. If callUserData of the X25Dte component is also null and protocolEncType of this Peer has the value IP, H.CC will be signalled as the call user data of a call request packet. Thus for IP encapsulation according to RFC1356, both the callUserData from the Peer and X25Dte components must be null and the protocolEncType set to IP.

mscX25DtePeerPEncTable.name: mscX25DtePeerPEncTable
mscX25DtePeerPEncTable.description: Each instance of this replicated attribute describes an encapsulation method permitted for encapsulating the protocol data units (PDUs) of an upper layer protocol when communicating with the remote host identified by this Peer component. The index of a given replicated instance of this attribute represents the relative priority of the encapsulation method specified by the given attribute instance. An attribute with index '1' has the highest priority, so the encapsulation method described by it will be the first one attempted when signalling a call to the link. If the protocolEncType is set to IP to encapsulate IP traffic according to RFC1356, the callUserData for this Peer component and the X25Dte component must both be null, so that H.CC will be signalled as the call user data of the call request. This indicates that the protocol encapsulation type of IP is to be used for the channel. A call received from the link will be accepted as long as the encapsulation method indicated in the call user data of the incoming call packet is included in one of these replicated attributes. (This presupposes that the incoming call has been directed to the RemoteGroup to which this Peer is linked through the linkToRemoteGroup attribute.)

mscX25DtePeerPEncIndex.name: mscX25DtePeerPEncIndex
mscX25DtePeerPEncIndex.description: This variable represents the index for the mscX25DtePeerPEncTable.

mscX25DtePeerPEncValue.name: mscX25DtePeerPEncValue
mscX25DtePeerPEncValue.description: This variable represents an individual value for the mscX25DtePeerPEncTable.

mscX25DtePeerPEncRowStatus.name: mscX25DtePeerPEncRowStatus
mscX25DtePeerPEncRowStatus.description: This variable is used to control the addition and deletion of individual values of the mscX25DtePeerPEncTable.

mscX25DtePeerLcnTable.name: mscX25DtePeerLcnTable
mscX25DtePeerLcnTable.description: This attribute specifies the local logical channel numbers (Lcn) in use for the X.25 calls to the remote host identified by this Peer component.

mscX25DtePeerLcnValue.name: mscX25DtePeerLcnValue
mscX25DtePeerLcnValue.description: This variable represents both the value and the index for the mscX25DtePeerLcnTable.

mscX25DtePLcnRowStatusTable.name: mscX25DtePLcnRowStatusTable
mscX25DtePLcnRowStatusTable.description: This entry controls the addition and deletion of mscX25DtePLcn components.

mscX25DtePLcnRowStatusEntry.name: mscX25DtePLcnRowStatusEntry
mscX25DtePLcnRowStatusEntry.description: A single entry in the table represents a single mscX25DtePLcn component.

mscX25DtePLcnRowStatus.name: mscX25DtePLcnRowStatus
mscX25DtePLcnRowStatus.description: This variable is used as the basis for SNMP naming of mscX25DtePLcn components. These components can be added and deleted.

mscX25DtePLcnComponentName.name: mscX25DtePLcnComponentName
mscX25DtePLcnComponentName.description: This variable provides the component's string name for use with the ASCII Console Interface

mscX25DtePLcnStorageType.name: mscX25DtePLcnStorageType
mscX25DtePLcnStorageType.description: This variable represents the storage type value for the mscX25DtePLcn tables.

mscX25DtePLcnIndex.name: mscX25DtePLcnIndex
mscX25DtePLcnIndex.description: This variable represents the index for the mscX25DtePLcn tables.

mscX25DtePLcnProvTable.name: mscX25DtePLcnProvTable
mscX25DtePLcnProvTable.description: This group contains the provisionable parameters for the permanent logical channels (PLcns) on the X.25 interface (corresponding to Permanent Virtual Circuits (PVCs) provisioned on the Wide Area Network).

mscX25DtePLcnEncAddressType.name: mscX25DtePLcnEncAddressType
mscX25DtePLcnEncAddressType.description: This attribute specifies the encapsulation type for the address of the remote host with which this Peer component allows communication.

mscX25DtePLcnEncAddress.name: mscX25DtePLcnEncAddress
mscX25DtePLcnEncAddress.description: This attribute specifies the encapsulation address of the remote host with which this PermLcn component defines a connection

mscX25DtePLcnProtocolEncType.name: mscX25DtePLcnProtocolEncType
mscX25DtePLcnProtocolEncType.description: This attribute specifies the encapsulation method to use when exchanging protocol data units (PDUs) over this channel. IP and Null protocolEncTypes are as defined in RFC1356. NscNull is an encapsulation method for carrying IP datagrams which requires removing 3 padding octets of zeroes and the protocol identifier H.CC from the front of each data packet received from the link in order to obtain the PDU. PDUs sent to the link are propounded by a the protocol identifier H.CC. NscNull should only be set when the remote host is following this same encapsulation method.

mscX25DtePLcnLinkToRemoteGroup.name: mscX25DtePLcnLinkToRemoteGroup
mscX25DtePLcnLinkToRemoteGroup.description: This attribute specifies the link to the RemoteGroup, indicating the RemoteGroup component with which this PermLcn component is associated. The RemoteGroup components logically divide up the X.25 Interface such that a number of Protocol Ports (and consequently a number of Virtual Routers) may share the same X.25 Interface into a Wide Area Network. In particular, the remote host identified by this PermLcn component is designated as belonging to the RemoteGroup linked by this attribute. The set of all PermLcn and Peer components which link to a given RemoteGroup determine the subset of remote hosts which are accessible to a particular Protocol Port (and ultimately a Virtual Router).

mscX25DtePLcnInPacketSize.name: mscX25DtePLcnInPacketSize
mscX25DtePLcnInPacketSize.description: This attribute specifies the maximum receive packet size in octets.

mscX25DtePLcnOutPacketSize.name: mscX25DtePLcnOutPacketSize
mscX25DtePLcnOutPacketSize.description: This attribute specifies the maximum transmit packet size in octets.

mscX25DtePLcnInWindowSize.name: mscX25DtePLcnInWindowSize
mscX25DtePLcnInWindowSize.description: This attribute specifies the maximum receive window size. A inWindowSize greater than 7 is only valid when the packetSequencing attribute of the X25Dte component is set to modulo128.

mscX25DtePLcnOutWindowSize.name: mscX25DtePLcnOutWindowSize
mscX25DtePLcnOutWindowSize.description: This attribute specifies the maximum transmit window size. A outWindowSize greater than 7 is only valid when the packetSequencing attribute of the X25Dte component is set to modulo128.

mscX25DteLcnRowStatusTable.name: mscX25DteLcnRowStatusTable
mscX25DteLcnRowStatusTable.description: *** THIS TABLE CURRENTLY NOT IMPLEMENTED *** This entry controls the addition and deletion of mscX25DteLcn components.

mscX25DteLcnRowStatusEntry.name: mscX25DteLcnRowStatusEntry
mscX25DteLcnRowStatusEntry.description: A single entry in the table represents a single mscX25DteLcn component.

mscX25DteLcnRowStatus.name: mscX25DteLcnRowStatus
mscX25DteLcnRowStatus.description: This variable is used as the basis for SNMP naming of mscX25DteLcn components. These components cannot be added nor deleted.

mscX25DteLcnComponentName.name: mscX25DteLcnComponentName
mscX25DteLcnComponentName.description: This variable provides the component's string name for use with the ASCII Console Interface

mscX25DteLcnStorageType.name: mscX25DteLcnStorageType
mscX25DteLcnStorageType.description: This variable represents the storage type value for the mscX25DteLcn tables.

mscX25DteLcnIndex.name: mscX25DteLcnIndex
mscX25DteLcnIndex.description: This variable represents the index for the mscX25DteLcn tables.

mscX25DteLcnStateTable.name: mscX25DteLcnStateTable
mscX25DteLcnStateTable.description: *** THIS TABLE CURRENTLY NOT IMPLEMENTED *** This group contains the three OSI State attributes. The descriptions generically indicate what each state attribute implies about the component. Note that not all the values and state combinations described here are supported by every component which uses this group. For component-specific information and the valid state combinations, refer to NTP 241-7001-150, Passport Operations and Maintenance Guide.

mscX25DteLcnAdminState.name: mscX25DteLcnAdminState
mscX25DteLcnAdminState.description: This attribute indicates the OSI Administrative State of the component. The value locked indicates that the component is administratively prohibited from providing services for its users. A Lock or Lock - force command has been previously issued for this component. When the value is locked, the value of usageState must be idle. The value shuttingDown indicates that the component is administratively permitted to provide service to its existing users only. A Lock command was issued against the component and it is in the process of shutting down. The value unlocked indicates that the component is administratively permitted to provide services for its users. To enter this state, issue an Unlock command to this component.

mscX25DteLcnOperationalState.name: mscX25DteLcnOperationalState
mscX25DteLcnOperationalState.description: This attribute indicates the OSI Operational State of the component. The value enabled indicates that the component is available for operation. Note that if adminState is locked, it would still not be providing service. The value disabled indicates that the component is not available for operation. For example, something is wrong with the component itself, or with another component on which this one depends. If the value is disabled, the usageState must be idle.

mscX25DteLcnUsageState.name: mscX25DteLcnUsageState
mscX25DteLcnUsageState.description: This attribute indicates the OSI Usage State of the component. The value idle indicates that the component is not currently in use. The value active indicates that the component is in use and has spare capacity to provide for additional users. The value busy indicates that the component is in use and has no spare operating capacity for additional users at this time.

mscX25DteLcnCpTable.name: mscX25DteLcnCpTable
mscX25DteLcnCpTable.description: *** THIS TABLE CURRENTLY NOT IMPLEMENTED *** This group contains the call parameters that are in use for this logical channel. For a PVC only the packet size and the window size attributes are meaningful.

mscX25DteLcnInPacketSize.name: mscX25DteLcnInPacketSize
mscX25DteLcnInPacketSize.description: This attribute indicates the maximum receive packet size in octets.

mscX25DteLcnOutPacketSize.name: mscX25DteLcnOutPacketSize
mscX25DteLcnOutPacketSize.description: This attribute indicates the maximum transmit packet size in octets.

mscX25DteLcnInWindowSize.name: mscX25DteLcnInWindowSize
mscX25DteLcnInWindowSize.description: This attribute indicates the receive window size.

mscX25DteLcnOutWindowSize.name: mscX25DteLcnOutWindowSize
mscX25DteLcnOutWindowSize.description: This attribute indicates the transmit window size.

mscX25DteLcnProposeReverseCharging.name: mscX25DteLcnProposeReverseCharging
mscX25DteLcnProposeReverseCharging.description: Specifies whether local/reverse charging was negotiated for this logical channel. To determine which end of the channel is paying for the call, this attribute must be examined in combination with the callDirection attribute. For example, if this attribute is set to reverse and the callDirection attribute indicates incoming, it means the incoming call signalled reverse charging, so the local end of the channel is being charged. On the other, if the value of this attribute is reverse and the callDirection is outgoing, it means that the call request sent to the link signalled reverse charging; so the remote end is charged. Similarly, a value of local must also be interpreted in combination with the callDirection to determine which end is being charged. If the value of the callDirection attribute is plcn, the proposeReverseCharging attribute is meaningless.

mscX25DteLcnFastSelect.name: mscX25DteLcnFastSelect
mscX25DteLcnFastSelect.description: This attribute indicates whether the fast select was used in establishing this logical channel.

mscX25DteLcnOutThroughputClassSize.name: mscX25DteLcnOutThroughputClassSize
mscX25DteLcnOutThroughputClassSize.description: This attribute specifies the transmit throughput class.

mscX25DteLcnInThroughputClassSize.name: mscX25DteLcnInThroughputClassSize
mscX25DteLcnInThroughputClassSize.description: This attribute specifies the receive throughput class.

mscX25DteLcnCugIndex.name: mscX25DteLcnCugIndex
mscX25DteLcnCugIndex.description: This attribute indicates the index of the Closed User Group facility used in establishing this logical channel.

mscX25DteLcnCugoaIndex.name: mscX25DteLcnCugoaIndex
mscX25DteLcnCugoaIndex.description: This attribute indicates the index of the Closed User Group with Outgoing Access facility used in establishing this logical channel.

mscX25DteLcnNetworkUserIdentifier.name: mscX25DteLcnNetworkUserIdentifier
mscX25DteLcnNetworkUserIdentifier.description: Specifies the Network User Identifier used for this logical channel.

mscX25DteLcnChargingInformation.name: mscX25DteLcnChargingInformation
mscX25DteLcnChargingInformation.description: This attribute indicates whether or not the charging information facility was used in establishing this logical channel. A value of notSpecified means the facility was not signalled. A value of notRequested means the facility was signalled but charging information was not requested (that is, the charging info field of the facility was set Off). A value of requested means the facility was signalled to explicitly request charging information. DESCRIPTION

mscX25DteLcnRpoa.name: mscX25DteLcnRpoa
mscX25DteLcnRpoa.description: This attribute indicates the RPOA facility which was signalled in establishing this logical channel.

mscX25DteLcnTrnstDlySlctnAInd.name: mscX25DteLcnTrnstDlySlctnAInd
mscX25DteLcnTrnstDlySlctnAInd.description: This attribute indicates the Transit Delay Selection and Indication value used for this logical channel. A value of 65536 means no facility was signalled.

mscX25DteLcnCallingNetworkFax.name: mscX25DteLcnCallingNetworkFax
mscX25DteLcnCallingNetworkFax.description: This attribute indicates the Calling Network facilities which were signalled in the call packet. A value of null (empty string) means no calling network facilities were signalled.

mscX25DteLcnCalledNetworkFax.name: mscX25DteLcnCalledNetworkFax
mscX25DteLcnCalledNetworkFax.description: This attribute indicates the called network facilities which were signalled in the call packet. A value of null (empty string) means no called network facilities were signalled.

mscX25DteLcnCallUserData.name: mscX25DteLcnCallUserData
mscX25DteLcnCallUserData.description: This attribute indicates the user data which was signalled in the call packet. A value of null (empty string) means no user data was signalled.

mscX25DteLcnLcnStatusTable.name: mscX25DteLcnLcnStatusTable
mscX25DteLcnLcnStatusTable.description: *** THIS TABLE CURRENTLY NOT IMPLEMENTED *** This group contains the status for an X.25 Logical Channel.

mscX25DteLcnStatus.name: mscX25DteLcnStatus
mscX25DteLcnStatus.description: This attribute indicates the current state of the logical channel.

mscX25DteLcnCallDirection.name: mscX25DteLcnCallDirection
mscX25DteLcnCallDirection.description: This attribute indicates the direction of the call that caused the establishment of this channel.

mscX25DteLcnCalledAddress.name: mscX25DteLcnCalledAddress
mscX25DteLcnCalledAddress.description: This attribute indicates the called X.25 address to which the call is established.

mscX25DteLcnCallingAddress.name: mscX25DteLcnCallingAddress
mscX25DteLcnCallingAddress.description: This attribute indicates the calling X.25 address from which the call originated

mscX25DteLcnOriginalCalledAddress.name: mscX25DteLcnOriginalCalledAddress
mscX25DteLcnOriginalCalledAddress.description: This attribute indicates the X.25 address of the originally called DTE to which the call was attempted. This could be different from the value of the calledAddress attribute in the case where the original call was redirected.

mscX25DteLcnStatsTable.name: mscX25DteLcnStatsTable
mscX25DteLcnStatsTable.description: *** THIS TABLE CURRENTLY NOT IMPLEMENTED *** This group contains the operational statistics for an X.25 Logical Channel.

mscX25DteLcnInUknownProtocols.name: mscX25DteLcnInUknownProtocols
mscX25DteLcnInUknownProtocols.description: This attribute counts the number packets received from link which were discareded because of an unkown or unsupported protocols.

mscX25DteLcnInDataOctets.name: mscX25DteLcnInDataOctets
mscX25DteLcnInDataOctets.description: This attribute counts the number of octets of user data received from the link.

mscX25DteLcnInDataPackets.name: mscX25DteLcnInDataPackets
mscX25DteLcnInDataPackets.description: This attribute counts the number of data packets received from the link.

mscX25DteLcnInRmtInitiatedRsts.name: mscX25DteLcnInRmtInitiatedRsts
mscX25DteLcnInRmtInitiatedRsts.description: This attribute counts the number of reset packets, with a cause code of 'DTE initiated', which were received from the link

mscX25DteLcnInPrvdrInitiatedRsts.name: mscX25DteLcnInPrvdrInitiatedRsts
mscX25DteLcnInPrvdrInitiatedRsts.description: This attribute counts the number of reset packets, with a cause code other than 'DTE initiated', which were received from the link.

mscX25DteLcnInInterruptPackets.name: mscX25DteLcnInInterruptPackets
mscX25DteLcnInInterruptPackets.description: This attribute counts the number of interrupt packets received from the link.

mscX25DteLcnOutDataOctets.name: mscX25DteLcnOutDataOctets
mscX25DteLcnOutDataOctets.description: This attribute counts the number of octets of user data sent to the link.

mscX25DteLcnOutDataPackets.name: mscX25DteLcnOutDataPackets
mscX25DteLcnOutDataPackets.description: This attribute counts the number of data packets sent to link.

mscX25DteLcnOutInterruptPackets.name: mscX25DteLcnOutInterruptPackets
mscX25DteLcnOutInterruptPackets.description: This attribute counts the number of interrupt packets sent to link.

mscX25DteLcnT22ResetTimeouts.name: mscX25DteLcnT22ResetTimeouts
mscX25DteLcnT22ResetTimeouts.description: This attribute counts the number of times the t22 reset timer has expired.

mscX25DteLapbRowStatusTable.name: mscX25DteLapbRowStatusTable
mscX25DteLapbRowStatusTable.description: This entry controls the addition and deletion of mscX25DteLapb components.

mscX25DteLapbRowStatusEntry.name: mscX25DteLapbRowStatusEntry
mscX25DteLapbRowStatusEntry.description: A single entry in the table represents a single mscX25DteLapb component.

mscX25DteLapbRowStatus.name: mscX25DteLapbRowStatus
mscX25DteLapbRowStatus.description: This variable is used as the basis for SNMP naming of mscX25DteLapb components. These components cannot be added nor deleted.

mscX25DteLapbComponentName.name: mscX25DteLapbComponentName
mscX25DteLapbComponentName.description: This variable provides the component's string name for use with the ASCII Console Interface

mscX25DteLapbStorageType.name: mscX25DteLapbStorageType
mscX25DteLapbStorageType.description: This variable represents the storage type value for the mscX25DteLapb tables.

mscX25DteLapbIndex.name: mscX25DteLapbIndex
mscX25DteLapbIndex.description: This variable represents the index for the mscX25DteLapb tables.

mscX25DteLapbCpTable.name: mscX25DteLapbCpTable
mscX25DteLapbCpTable.description: X25Dte/n Lapb This group contains the set of configuration parameters for the LAPB interface.

mscX25DteLapbStationType.name: mscX25DteLapbStationType
mscX25DteLapbStationType.description: This attribute specifies the DCE or the DTE role of operation for the LAPB interface. Changing this attribute will cause the lapb link to Reset.

mscX25DteLapbFrameSequencing.name: mscX25DteLapbFrameSequencing
mscX25DteLapbFrameSequencing.description: This attribute specifies the modulo of the frame sequence numbering of the LAPB interface. Changing this attribute will cause the lapb link to Reset.

mscX25DteLapbN1FrameSize.name: mscX25DteLapbN1FrameSize
mscX25DteLapbN1FrameSize.description: This attribute specifies the maximum frame size in bits that can be transmitted or received. This value must be greater than or equal to the maximum packet size across the interface(in bits)+ max level 3 header size(in bits)+ max level 2 header size(in bits)+ crc in bits. (max Pkt size + -------------> 4096*8 max level 3 header size + ---> 4*8 level 2 header size + --------> 5*8 crc -------------------> 2*8)

mscX25DteLapbKWindowSize.name: mscX25DteLapbKWindowSize
mscX25DteLapbKWindowSize.description: This attribute specifies the window size. This is the maximum number of unacknowledged sequenced frames that may be outstanding from or to this interface at any one time. A window size of greater than 7 is only valid when the sequence numbering of frames is modulo 128.

mscX25DteLapbN2TransmitLimit.name: mscX25DteLapbN2TransmitLimit
mscX25DteLapbN2TransmitLimit.description: This attribute specifies the maximum number of times a frame can be transmitted before appropriate recovery action is taken.

mscX25DteLapbT1AckTimer.name: mscX25DteLapbT1AckTimer
mscX25DteLapbT1AckTimer.description: This attribute specifies the period in milliseconds within which an acknowledgment of a sent frame must be received. The value set for t1 ack timer must be less than the value set for the t4 idle probe timer.

mscX25DteLapbT2AckDelayTimer.name: mscX25DteLapbT2AckDelayTimer
mscX25DteLapbT2AckDelayTimer.description: This attribute specifies the maximum period in milliseconds permissible to wait before sending an acknowledgment for a received in sequenced I-frame. A value of 0 means there will be no delay in acknowledgment.

mscX25DteLapbT4IdleProbeTimer.name: mscX25DteLapbT4IdleProbeTimer
mscX25DteLapbT4IdleProbeTimer.description: This attribute specifies the time period in milliseconds the link will be permitted to remain idle (that is, no frames are exchanged on the data link). Upon expiry of this timer, LAPB will poll its peer for status. The value set for t4 idle probe timer must be greater than the value set for the t1 ack timer.

mscX25DteLapbActionInitiate.name: mscX25DteLapbActionInitiate
mscX25DteLapbActionInitiate.description: This attribute specifies the action to be taken by the LAPB interface to initiate link setup.

mscX25DteLapbActionRecvDM.name: mscX25DteLapbActionRecvDM
mscX25DteLapbActionRecvDM.description: This attribute specifies the action to be taken by the LAPB interface when it receives a DM response.

mscX25DteLapbTxQDegradeThreshold.name: mscX25DteLapbTxQDegradeThreshold
mscX25DteLapbTxQDegradeThreshold.description: This attribute specifies the threshold of the number of higher layer packets queued, beyond which LAPB should initiate a service degrade alarm. A value of 65536 means no threshold.

mscX25DteLapbTxQResetThreshold.name: mscX25DteLapbTxQResetThreshold
mscX25DteLapbTxQResetThreshold.description: This attribute specifies the threshold of the number of higher layer packets queued, beyond which LAPB should initiate an overload alarm and reset the link. A value of 65536 means no threshold.

mscX25DteLapbStateTable.name: mscX25DteLapbStateTable
mscX25DteLapbStateTable.description: This group contains the three OSI State attributes. The descriptions generically indicate what each state attribute implies about the component. Note that not all the values and state combinations described here are supported by every component which uses this group. For component-specific information and the valid state combinations, refer to NTP 241-7001-150, Passport Operations and Maintenance Guide.

mscX25DteLapbAdminState.name: mscX25DteLapbAdminState
mscX25DteLapbAdminState.description: This attribute indicates the OSI Administrative State of the component. The value locked indicates that the component is administratively prohibited from providing services for its users. A Lock or Lock - force command has been previously issued for this component. When the value is locked, the value of usageState must be idle. The value shuttingDown indicates that the component is administratively permitted to provide service to its existing users only. A Lock command was issued against the component and it is in the process of shutting down. The value unlocked indicates that the component is administratively permitted to provide services for its users. To enter this state, issue an Unlock command to this component.

mscX25DteLapbOperationalState.name: mscX25DteLapbOperationalState
mscX25DteLapbOperationalState.description: This attribute indicates the OSI Operational State of the component. The value enabled indicates that the component is available for operation. Note that if adminState is locked, it would still not be providing service. The value disabled indicates that the component is not available for operation. For example, something is wrong with the component itself, or with another component on which this one depends. If the value is disabled, the usageState must be idle.

mscX25DteLapbUsageState.name: mscX25DteLapbUsageState
mscX25DteLapbUsageState.description: This attribute indicates the OSI Usage State of the component. The value idle indicates that the component is not currently in use. The value active indicates that the component is in use and has spare capacity to provide for additional users. The value busy indicates that the component is in use and has no spare operating capacity for additional users at this time.

mscX25DteLapbStatusTable.name: mscX25DteLapbStatusTable
mscX25DteLapbStatusTable.description: This group contains the status for the LAPB interface.

mscX25DteLapbCurrentState.name: mscX25DteLapbCurrentState
mscX25DteLapbCurrentState.description: This attribute specifies the current state of the LAPB interface.

mscX25DteLapbLastStateChangeReason.name: mscX25DteLapbLastStateChangeReason
mscX25DteLapbLastStateChangeReason.description: This attribute specifies the reason for the most recent state change.

mscX25DteLapbFrmrTransmit.name: mscX25DteLapbFrmrTransmit
mscX25DteLapbFrmrTransmit.description: This attribute specifies the Information field of the FRMR most recently sent.

mscX25DteLapbFrmrReceive.name: mscX25DteLapbFrmrReceive
mscX25DteLapbFrmrReceive.description: This attribute specifies the Information field of the FRMR most recently received.

mscX25DteLapbCurrentQueueSize.name: mscX25DteLapbCurrentQueueSize
mscX25DteLapbCurrentQueueSize.description: This attribute specifies the number of packets on the lapb transmit queue.

mscX25DteLapbStatsTable.description: This group contains the statistics for the LAPB interface.

mscX25DteLapbStateChanges.description: This attribute counts the number of times LAPB state has changed. Refer to the attribute 'linkState' for the set of possible states.

mscX25DteLapbRemoteBusy.name: mscX25DteLapbRemoteBusy
mscX25DteLapbRemoteBusy.description: This attribute counts the number of times transmission of an I-frame was un-successful due to a perceived remote busy condition (window closed or remote busy).

mscX25DteLapbTransmitRejectFrames.name: mscX25DteLapbTransmitRejectFrames
mscX25DteLapbTransmitRejectFrames.description: This attribute counts the number of REJ frames sent by the interface.

mscX25DteLapbReceiveRejectFrames.name: mscX25DteLapbReceiveRejectFrames
mscX25DteLapbReceiveRejectFrames.description: This attribute counts the number of REJ frames received by the interface.

mscX25DteLapbT1AckTimeout.name: mscX25DteLapbT1AckTimeout
mscX25DteLapbT1AckTimeout.description: This attribute counts the number of times the T1 timer has expired.

mscX25DteLapbFramerRowStatus.description: This variable is used as the basis for SNMP naming of mscX25DteLapbFramer components. These components cannot be added nor deleted.

mscX25DteLapbFramerComponentName.description: This variable provides the component's string name for use with the ASCII Console Interface

mscX25DteLapbFramerStorageType.description: This variable represents the storage type value for the mscX25DteLapbFramer tables.

mscX25DteLapbFramerIndex.name: mscX25DteLapbFramerIndex
mscX25DteLapbFramerIndex.description: This variable represents the index for the mscX25DteLapbFramer tables.

mscX25DteLapbFramerProvTable.name: mscX25DteLapbFramerProvTable
mscX25DteLapbFramerProvTable.description: This group contains the base provisioning data for the Framer component. Application or hardware interface specific provisioning data is contained in other provisionable Framer groups.

mscX25DteLapbFramerInterfaceName.name: mscX25DteLapbFramerInterfaceName
mscX25DteLapbFramerInterfaceName.description: This attribute contains a hardware component name. The attribute associates the application with a specific link. This defines the module processor on which Framer's parent component (as well as Framer itself) will run.

mscX25DteLapbFramerLinkTable.name: mscX25DteLapbFramerLinkTable
mscX25DteLapbFramerLinkTable.description: This group contains attributes defining the framing of data on the link interface.

mscX25DteLapbFramerFlagsBetweenFrames.name: mscX25DteLapbFramerFlagsBetweenFrames
mscX25DteLapbFramerFlagsBetweenFrames.description: This attribute defines the number of flags that are inserted between frames sent to the link interface.

mscX25DteLapbFramerStateTable.name: mscX25DteLapbFramerStateTable
mscX25DteLapbFramerStateTable.description: This group contains the three OSI State attributes. The descriptions generically indicate what each state attribute implies about the component. Note that not all the values and state combinations described here are supported by every component which uses this group. For component-specific information and the valid state combinations, refer to NTP 241-7001-150, Passport Operations and Maintenance Guide.

mscX25DteLapbFramerAdminState.name: mscX25DteLapbFramerAdminState
mscX25DteLapbFramerAdminState.description: This attribute indicates the OSI Administrative State of the component. The value locked indicates that the component is administratively prohibited from providing services for its users. A Lock or Lock - force command has been previously issued for this component. When the value is locked, the value of usageState must be idle. The value shuttingDown indicates that the component is administratively permitted to provide service to its existing users only. A Lock command was issued against the component and it is in the process of shutting down. The value unlocked indicates that the component is administratively permitted to provide services for its users. To enter this state, issue an Unlock command to this component.

mscX25DteLapbFramerOperationalState.name: mscX25DteLapbFramerOperationalState
mscX25DteLapbFramerOperationalState.description: This attribute indicates the OSI Operational State of the component. The value enabled indicates that the component is available for operation. Note that if adminState is locked, it would still not be providing service. The value disabled indicates that the component is not available for operation. For example, something is wrong with the component itself, or with another component on which this one depends. If the value is disabled, the usageState must be idle.

mscX25DteLapbFramerUsageState.name: mscX25DteLapbFramerUsageState
mscX25DteLapbFramerUsageState.description: This attribute indicates the OSI Usage State of the component. The value idle indicates that the component is not currently in use. The value active indicates that the component is in use and has spare capacity to provide for additional users. The value busy indicates that the component is in use and has no spare operating capacity for additional users at this time.

mscX25DteLapbFramerStatsTable.name: mscX25DteLapbFramerStatsTable
mscX25DteLapbFramerStatsTable.description: This group contains the operational statistics data for a Framer component.

mscX25DteLapbFramerFrmToIf.name: mscX25DteLapbFramerFrmToIf
mscX25DteLapbFramerFrmToIf.description: The number of frames transmitted to the link interface by Framer. Note: This does not include the number of frames transmitted directly to the hardware queue, thus bypassing the Framer component.

mscX25DteLapbFramerFrmFromIf.name: mscX25DteLapbFramerFrmFromIf
mscX25DteLapbFramerFrmFromIf.description: The number of frames received from the link interface by Framer.

mscX25DteLapbFramerOctetFromIf.name: mscX25DteLapbFramerOctetFromIf
mscX25DteLapbFramerOctetFromIf.description: The number of bytes received from the link interface by Framer.

mscX25DteLapbFramerAborts.name: mscX25DteLapbFramerAborts
mscX25DteLapbFramerAborts.description: This attribute is the total number of aborts received.

mscX25DteLapbFramerCrcErrors.name: mscX25DteLapbFramerCrcErrors
mscX25DteLapbFramerCrcErrors.description: This attribute is the total number of frames with CRC errors, occurring in the receive direction from the link.

mscX25DteLapbFramerLrcErrors.name: mscX25DteLapbFramerLrcErrors
mscX25DteLapbFramerLrcErrors.description: This attribute is the total number of frames with LRC errors, occurring in the Tx link prior to transmission onto the link.

mscX25DteLapbFramerNonOctetErrors.name: mscX25DteLapbFramerNonOctetErrors
mscX25DteLapbFramerNonOctetErrors.description: This attribute is the total number of frames that were non octet aligned.

mscX25DteLapbFramerOverruns.name: mscX25DteLapbFramerOverruns
mscX25DteLapbFramerOverruns.description: This attribute is the total number of frames received from the link for which overruns occurred.

mscX25DteLapbFramerUnderruns.name: mscX25DteLapbFramerUnderruns
mscX25DteLapbFramerUnderruns.description: This attribute is the total number of frames transmitted to the link for which underruns occurred.

mscX25DteLapbFramerFrmToIf64.name: mscX25DteLapbFramerFrmToIf64
mscX25DteLapbFramerFrmToIf64.description: The number of frames transmitted to the link interface by Framer. Note: This does not include the number of frames transmitted directly to the hardware queue, thus bypassing the Framer component.

mscX25DteLapbFramerFrmFromIf64.name: mscX25DteLapbFramerFrmFromIf64
mscX25DteLapbFramerFrmFromIf64.description: The number of frames received from the link interface by Framer.

mscX25DteLapbFramerOctetFromIf64.name: mscX25DteLapbFramerOctetFromIf64
mscX25DteLapbFramerOctetFromIf64.description: The number of bytes received from the link interface by Framer.

mscX25DteLapbFramerUtilTable.name: mscX25DteLapbFramerUtilTable
mscX25DteLapbFramerUtilTable.description: This group contains the link utilizaiton operational data for a Framer component.

mscX25DteLapbFramerNormPrioLinkUtilToIf.name: mscX25DteLapbFramerNormPrioLinkUtilToIf
mscX25DteLapbFramerNormPrioLinkUtilToIf.description: This attribute is the utilization of the normal and high priority data traffic (interruptable traffic) sent to the link as a percentage of the available bandwidth on the link. Note that this includes traffic with Transfer Priorities of 0, 6 and 9 and/or Emission Priority of 2 and 3. The utilization is the average for the last minute.

mscX25DteLapbFramerNormPrioLinkUtilFromI.name: mscX25DteLapbFramerNormPrioLinkUtilFromIf
mscX25DteLapbFramerNormPrioLinkUtilFromI.description: This attribute is the utilization of the normal and high priority data traffic (interruptable traffic) received from the link as a percentage of the available bandwidth on the link. Note that this includes traffic with Transfer Priorities of 0, 6 and 9 and/or Emission Priority of 2 and 3. The utilization is the average for the last minute.

mscX25DtePleInactivityTimer.description: This attribute specifies the period in milliseconds this interface will keep an idle connection open before closing it.

mscX25DtePleOpTable.name: mscX25DtePleOpTable
mscX25DtePleOpTable.description: This group contains the Operational attributes relevant to an interface used to carry Multiprotocol Interconnect traffic over X.25.

mscX25DtePleEncAddrToX25LkupFlrs.name: mscX25DtePleEncAddrToX25LkupFlrs
mscX25DtePleEncAddrToX25LkupFlrs.description: This attribute indicates the number of times a translation attempt from an Encapsulation address to an X.25 address failed to find a corresponding X.25 address. Such a failure could occur when a Protocol Port, linked to a RemoteGroup via the linkToProtocolPort attribute of the RemoteGroup, requests through the software that a X.25 call be established to a particular Encapsulation address. If the RemoteGroup does not have a Peer component linked in its linkToPeer attribute list, with the encAddress attribute equal to the Encapsulation address specified, this counter will be incremented, because the corresponding Peer component needed to establish an X.25 connection was not found.

mscX25DtePleLastFailedEncAddr.name: mscX25DtePleLastFailedEncAddr
mscX25DtePleLastFailedEncAddr.description: This attribute indicates the last Encapsulation address for which no corresponding X.25 address was found and thus caused encAddressToX25LkupFlrs to be incremented.

mscX25DtePleX25AddrToEncLkupFlrs.name: mscX25DtePleX25AddrToEncLkupFlrs
mscX25DtePleX25AddrToEncLkupFlrs.description: This attribute indicates the number of times a translation attempt from an X.25 address to an Encapsulation address failed to find a corresponding Encapsulation address. Such a failure could occur when a incoming call received from the link by the X.25 DTE is directed to a specific RemoteGroup because the called address matches the localAddress attribute of the RemoteGroup component. If the RemoteGroup component does not have a Peer component linked in its linkToPeer attribute list, with the x25Address attribute equal to the calling address from the incoming call packet, there is no appropriate Peer component, so the call is cleared and this counter is incremented.

mscX25DtePleLastFailedX25Addr.name: mscX25DtePleLastFailedX25Addr
mscX25DtePleLastFailedX25Addr.description: This field specifies the last X.25 address that caused x25AddressToEncLkupFlrs to be incremented.

mscX25DteRgIfAdminStatus.description: The desired state of the interface. The up state indicates the interface is operational. The down state indicates the interface is not operational. The testing state indicates that no operational packets can be passed.

mscX25DteRgProvTable.name: mscX25DteRgProvTable
mscX25DteRgProvTable.description: This group contains the provisionable attributes of the RemoteGroup component.

mscX25DteRgLinkToProtocolPort.name: mscX25DteRgLinkToProtocolPort
mscX25DteRgLinkToProtocolPort.description: This attribute contains a protocol port component name. The attribute associates the application with a protocol port.

mscX25DteRgLocalAddress.name: mscX25DteRgLocalAddress
mscX25DteRgLocalAddress.description: This attribute contains the unique X.25 address which identifies this RemoteGroup. It should correspond to the called address in X.25 incoming call packets which are to be directed to this RemoteGroup. This allows calls received from the link to be directed to the appropriate RemoteGroup based on the called address in the X.25 call packet. The RemoteGroup components allow the X.25 interface to be shared amongst a number of Protocol Ports (and ultimately Virtual Routers) because each RemoteGroup is coupled with a specific ProtocolPort through its linkToProtocolPort attribute.

mscX25DteRgMtuSize.name: mscX25DteRgMtuSize
mscX25DteRgMtuSize.description: This attribute specifies the Maximum Transmit Unit (MTU); that is, the size of the largest datagram (in octets) which can be sent/ received on the interface.

mscX25DteRgStateTable.name: mscX25DteRgStateTable
mscX25DteRgStateTable.description: This group contains the three OSI State attributes. The descriptions generically indicate what each state attribute implies about the component. Note that not all the values and state combinations described here are supported by every component which uses this group. For component-specific information and the valid state combinations, refer to NTP 241-7001-150, Passport Operations and Maintenance Guide.

mscX25DteRgAdminState.name: mscX25DteRgAdminState
mscX25DteRgAdminState.description: This attribute indicates the OSI Administrative State of the component. The value locked indicates that the component is administratively prohibited from providing services for its users. A Lock or Lock - force command has been previously issued for this component. When the value is locked, the value of usageState must be idle. The value shuttingDown indicates that the component is administratively permitted to provide service to its existing users only. A Lock command was issued against the component and it is in the process of shutting down. The value unlocked indicates that the component is administratively permitted to provide services for its users. To enter this state, issue an Unlock command to this component.

mscX25DteRgOperationalState.name: mscX25DteRgOperationalState
mscX25DteRgOperationalState.description: This attribute indicates the OSI Operational State of the component. The value enabled indicates that the component is available for operation. Note that if adminState is locked, it would still not be providing service. The value disabled indicates that the component is not available for operation. For example, something is wrong with the component itself, or with another component on which this one depends. If the value is disabled, the usageState must be idle.

mscX25DteRgUsageState.name: mscX25DteRgUsageState
mscX25DteRgUsageState.description: This attribute indicates the OSI Usage State of the component. The value idle indicates that the component is not currently in use. The value active indicates that the component is in use and has spare capacity to provide for additional users. The value busy indicates that the component is in use and has no spare operating capacity for additional users at this time.

mscX25DteRgOperStatusTable.name: mscX25DteRgOperStatusTable
mscX25DteRgOperStatusTable.description: This group includes the Operational Status attribute. This attribute defines the current operational state of this component.

mscX25DteRgSnmpOperStatus.name: mscX25DteRgSnmpOperStatus
mscX25DteRgSnmpOperStatus.description: The current state of the interface. The up state indicates the interface is operational and capable of forwarding packets. The down state indicates the interface is not operational, thus unable to forward packets. testing state indicates that no operational packets can be passed.

mscX25DteRgLTPlcnTable.name: mscX25DteRgLTPlcnTable
mscX25DteRgLTPlcnTable.description: This attribute is a list of links to PermLcn components. The set of all Peer and PermLcn components which link to a given RemoteGroup determine the subset of remote hosts which are accessible to a particular Protocol Port (and ultimately a Virtual Router).

mscX25DteRgLTPlcnValue.name: mscX25DteRgLTPlcnValue
mscX25DteRgLTPlcnValue.description: This variable represents both the value and the index for the mscX25DteRgLTPlcnTable.

mscX25DteRgLTPlcnRowStatus.name: mscX25DteRgLTPlcnRowStatus
mscX25DteRgLTPlcnRowStatus.description: This variable is used to control the addition and deletion of individual values of the mscX25DteRgLTPlcnTable.

mscX25DteRgLtPeerTable.name: mscX25DteRgLtPeerTable
mscX25DteRgLtPeerTable.description: This attribute gives a list of links to Peer components. The set of all Peer and PermLcn components which link to a given RemoteGroup determine the subset of remote hosts which are accessible to a particular Protocol Port (and ultimately a Virtual Router).

mscX25DteRgLtPeerValue.name: mscX25DteRgLtPeerValue
mscX25DteRgLtPeerValue.description: This variable represents both the value and the index for the mscX25DteRgLtPeerTable.

mscX25DteRgLtPeerRowStatus.name: mscX25DteRgLtPeerRowStatus

mscX25DteRgLcnTable.name: mscX25DteRgLcnTable
mscX25DteRgLcnTable.description: This attribute lists the Lcn components for the X25Dte, which belong to this RemoteGroup. There is an Lcn component listed here for every lcn connection belonging to this RemoteGroup. The lcns were established using either a Peer component linked to this RemoteGroup (in response to a switched call) or using a PermLcn component linked to this RemoteGroup (a permanent connection).

mscX25DteRgLcnValue.name: mscX25DteRgLcnValue
